data.title: Watch Camp Rock (2008) Full Movie Online
data.meta_description: Where to watch Camp Rock (2008) starring Demi Lovato, Joe Jonas, Meaghan Jette Martin and directed by Matthew Diamond.
data.text:
Entertainment WeeklyGillian Flynn

Camp Rock is so rigidly formulaic, so unremarkable, that by the time the cast sings its finale, "We Rock," it's hard to agree.

Groucho ReviewsPeter Canavese

[A] derisive discussion of 'stupid cookie-cutter pop star stuff' is more than a little ironic in this Radio Disney petri dish, but at least the Jonas Brothers are a class act.

DVDTalk.comDavid Cornelius

There's a terrific cast but nothing for them to do but waddle through your average Disney Channel blandness.

VarietyBrian Lowry

Camp Rock is the kind of confection that requires copious brushing and flossing immediately afterward, but given Disney's track record, that won't dissuade four out of five girls with Jonas Brothers fever from sinking their teeth right in.

New York PostAustin Smith

It's really a great movie, like a modern-day version of an old Judy Garland-Mickey Rooney picture in which the kids put on a show that improves the lives of all who see it.

New York TimesNeil Genzlinger

The movie has some bright spots, but so much of it revolves around the resident diva of the title camp that it's hard to focus on the good stuff; you're too annoyed at having this lazily imagined character shoved down your throat for the zillionth time.

Houston ChronicleJoey Guerra

Camp Rock is exactly what you'd expect it to be: silly, sometimes sweet, occasionally confusing, aggressively perky and brimming with disposable pop songs about being true to yourself.

Los Angeles TimesRobert Lloyd

Camp Rock" isn't particularly good, but it's good at what it does. The product may be "inauthentic," if such a thing is even possible, but the way it will connect with a lot of little girls and more than a few little boys is real enough.

Pittsburgh Post-GazetteGretchen McKay

Demi Lovato has all the requirements for Disney stardom, but she doesn't really act so much as walk through this movie, stopping occasionally to flash a larger than life smile.
